This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it introduces a new regularizer for auto-encoders. It may also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it deals with neural networks. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as auto-encoders are a popular topic in AI research. The paper also mentions the use of activation functions in image processing, which could place it under cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper discusses the connections between the proposed method and other types of auto-encoders, which could place it under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
